properties.title: Mozart Cafe Cluj
properties.description: Restaurant/cafe shop with a cute piano. The piano is not well tuned, but if you want to play it, ask the staff and they will let you play. It will take some time to get used to the sound and eventually it will sound good enough.

properties.title: Herne Hill
properties.description:
Featured in the film, this beautiful and unique piano was introduced to Herne Hill Station in 2012. It can be found in the underpass, just next to the flower shop.
A recent Crowdfunding campaign run by the Herne Hill Forum raised enough money to enable a brand new piano to be bought for location - and will be introduced in early October!

properties.title: St Pancras, The Arcade
properties.description:
Situated next to the Eurostar entrance on the main shopping arcade, this great sounding piano is very well maintained by the station, and extremely popular with commuters passing through. 
The first piano here was introduced in 2009, and unlike some of the other public pianos, it is accessible throughout the night.

properties.title: St Pancras no. 2, The Arcade
properties.description:
There are three pianos in total at St Pancras International. This one is further down towards the trains, next to the MAC shop. 

Like the other two pianos and the station that they're in, this piano is available to use 24 hours a day.

properties.title: St Pancras no. 3
properties.description: This last St Pancras piano is, like the other two, maintained by the station. At the moment it's located just by the Starbucks, overlooking the escalators that go down to the underground or up to platforms 11-13.

properties.title: The Oracle, Reading
properties.description:
This piano is situated just outside the Five Guys restaurant in the Oracle shopping centre, up on the first floor. 
It's another great sounding, relatively new piano, available for all to play during the centres opening hours.

properties.title: Forest Hill
properties.description:
The Forest Hill piano is just by the station under the bicycle shelter. It was introduced as part of the 'Jack in the Box' community project. 
See the Forest Hill society's website: http://www.foresthillsociety.com/2014/04/forest-hill-street-piano.html

properties.title: Crossrail Place Sky Garden, Canary Wharf
properties.description:
You can find this piano upstairs in the Crossrail Place building. It moves about, so you might have to look around but it shouldn't be too tricky. 

In the past Fabio Tedde - the 'Pianist Without Borders', who features in our doc - has called impromptu jam sessions here. The second and third pictures are of one such evening, and if he calls some more we HIGHLY recommend you going if you can!! Have a look at Fabio's website here: http://www.pianistwithoutborders.com/

properties.title: Marylebone Station
properties.description:
This upright in Marylebone National Rail station is lovely and not used very often - maybe a good option if you want to get some playing time. We've heard that it was donated to the station by a train driver who thought it would be a welcome addition for commuters and station workers alike. 

If you have time, have a look at this really great feature in the Marylebone Journal who interviewed a few players: http://www.marylebonevillage.com/marylebone-journal/key-workers

properties.title: Crossrail Place West End Lobby, First Floor, Canary Wharf
properties.description:
This piano is amazing. It was designed by Stelios Manganis as part of Canary Wharf's Play Me, I'm Your's exhibition by Luke Jerram in 2015. 

Have a look at Manganis' website - he's done some really interesting stuff: http://www.steliosmanganis.com/

properties.title: Sheffield Train Station
properties.description: There are TWO lovely upright pianos in Sheffield train station available to play. They are opposite the Upper Crust and Caffe Ritazza.

properties.title: Brighton Station
properties.description: Brighton Train Station's upright street piano can be found just by one of the main entrances, by the Upper Crust.

properties.title: Heathrow Airport Terminal 4
properties.description: We've heard this piano is great to play - but also that it moves around a lot! If you know it's current exact location let us know! (on twitter @livestreetpiano or facebook Instrument of Change: Street Piano)
